==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cow-cockle
<hw>cow-cockle</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a European annual (<spn>Vaccaria
hispanica</spn>) with pale rose-colored flowers; cultivated flower or
self-sown grainfield weed; introduced in North America; sometimes
classified as a soapwort.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cowherb, cow cockle, <spn>Vaccaria hispanica</spn>,
<spn>Vaccaria pyramidata</spn>, <spn>Saponaria vaccaria</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowdie</ent>⟦br⟧
